     3‚Üí## Getting Started
     4‚Üí
     5‚ÜíFirst, run the development server:
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí```bash
     8‚Üínpm run dev
     9‚Üí# or
    10‚Üíyarn dev
    11‚Üí# or
    12‚Üípnpm dev
    13‚Üí```
    14‚Üí
    15‚ÜíOpen [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) with your browser to see the result.
    16‚Üí
    17‚ÜíYou can start editing the page by modifying `app/page.tsx`. The page auto-updates as you edit the file.
    18‚Üí
    19‚Üí[API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) can be accessed on [http://localhost:3000/api/hello](http://localhost:3000/api/hello). This endpoint can be edited in `pages/api/hello.ts`.
    20‚Üí
    21‚ÜíThe `pages/api` directory is mapped to `/api/*`. Files in this directory are treated as [API routes](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-routes/introduction) instead of React pages.
    22‚Üí
    23‚ÜíThis project uses [`next/font`](https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/font-optimization) to automatically optimize and load Inter, a custom Google Font.
    24‚Üí
